  <main id="main">
    <article class="content">

      <section id="college" class="card section">
        <h2>College Career</h2>
        <p>
          As a true freshman at LSU in 2021, Nabers played in 11 games with six starts and had 28 receptions for 417 yards
          and four touchdowns. He returned to LSU as a starter in 2022; Nabers was named MVP of the 2023 Citrus Bowl with
          nine catches for 163 yards and a touchdown pass to Jayden Daniels. In 2023 he posted 13 receptions for 239 yards
          and two TDs vs. Mississippi State and finished as a unanimous All-American, leading the FBS with 1,569 receiving
          yards. He declared for the 2024 NFL Draft and finished as LSU’s all-time leader in receiving yards (3,003).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="rookie" class="card section">
        <h2>Rookie Year</h2>
        <p>
          Drafted sixth overall by the Giants in 2024, Nabers set franchise marks and earned a 2025 Pro Bowl selection.
          With a new QB in year two, expectations are <em>even higher</em> for continued growth.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="records" class="card section">
        <h2>Records Set</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Most receptions by a rookie WR in a single season: 109</li>
          <li>Youngest WR with multiple touchdowns in a game: 21 years and 56 days</li>
          <li>Fastest to reach 100 career receptions: 14 games (tied with Odell Beckham Jr.)</li>
          <li>Most targets by a rookie in a season: 170</li>
          <li>Most receptions at home by a rookie in a season: 58</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

